
# test_continue_pre_next_turn.hms
#
# Scripts the deterministic portion of the Continue-and-Save flow (name the
# home city, patrol the starting stack), then hands control back to the human
# player via `end` so the rest of the session can be played manually and
# captured with `--record`.
#
# Usage:
#   ReMoMber --continue --scenario test_continue_pre_next_turn.hms --record next_turn.RMR
#
# The scenario stops after the Patrol click.  The game is still running and
# sitting on the Main Screen with all starting units patrolled — ready for a
# Next Turn click and whatever else you want to capture manually.
#
# To exit, play out whatever you want then quit normally from within the game;
# the .RMR file will be finalized when Screen_Control returns.

# === Home city naming popup ===
wait 500ms                # let the popup finish loading
backspace                 # clear the random pre-filled city name
type Claudesville
enter                     # confirm the name; popup closes

wait 500ms                # let the popup close and the Main Screen settle

# === Main Screen: patrol the active unit stack ===
click 290 180             # Patrol button (rect ~280,176 - 313,186)
wait 300ms                # let the patrol action take effect

# Scenario ends here without quitting — control hands back to the human.
end
